1
00:00:01,167 --> 00:00:03,333
<i> Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!</i>

2
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,000
<i> What are you doing?
Hey, Edward!</i>

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,033
<i>- Hey, Edward! Edward!
- [WATER SPLASHES]</i>

4
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:08,533
<i> This is a meeting!</i>

5
00:00:08,533 --> 00:00:11,000
<i> Let's do our meeting here!</i>

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,400
<i>You're angry because I
overshadowed you?</i>

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>- No.
- No, you seem mad!</i>

8
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,300
<i>Who are you to reveal
that I used to be a DJ?</i>

9
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:21,100
<i>- It's true, isn't it?
- Welcome to Isla... Solara!</i>

10
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,367
- [SLAPS]
- Do you have a boyfriend?

11
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:24,233
<i> You are unbelievable!</i>

12
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:26,600
<i>Where are you going?
The tour isn't over yet!</i>

13
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:29,100
<i> Please sign the permit.</i>

14
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:32,300
[SIGH]<i> If it weren't
</i> for your grandfather!

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:40,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:54,567
Hey, long time no see.

17
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,733
It looks like you're here too.

18
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,367
You knew I'd be here.

19
00:00:58,367 --> 00:01:00,200
[BOK CHUCKLES] No.

20
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,100
I was surprised
by your presence.

21
00:01:04,167 --> 00:01:06,433
What are you doing here?

22
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:08,400
[BOK] I'm on a vacation!

23
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:09,700
Is that not allowed?

24
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:12,167
And there's a music fest, bro!

25
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:14,233
You know
that's my thing, right?

26
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:21,167
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

27
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:19,267
[GIO] Let's talk there.

28
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:27,467
Fine.

29
00:02:27,467 --> 00:02:28,833
Let's talk.

30
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:30,400
You look like you might cry.

31
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:34,867
I'll just get the money
you owe me.

32
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:37,800
Since someone told me
you're already rich.

33
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,433
Do you own this hotel?

34
00:02:39,433 --> 00:02:41,800
Didn't I tell you to wait?

35
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,500
I'll pay you, Bok.

36
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,200
Chill.

37
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,700
Okay, fine.

38
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,900
I can wait.

39
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:51,200
But while I'm waiting...

40
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,367
why don't we stay at the hotel?

41
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:53,800
There's nothing wrong
with that, right?

42
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:57,333
There are other hotels here,
why don't you stay there?

43
00:02:57,333 --> 00:03:00,767
[BOK] How will I keep an eye
on you if I'm far away?

44
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:03,767
C'mon? It's like
we don't have a history.

45
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:09,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,667
Get out of here.

47
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:14,167
[LUNA] Hi, Sir. Welcome to
Hotel 88. Have you checked in?

48
00:03:14,167 --> 00:03:15,900
Oh, not yet.

49
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,667
- Shall we?
- [LUNA] Yes, sir. This way.

50
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:18,600
Alright.

51
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,733
[LUNA] How many guests
are there? Three?

52
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,333
[BOK] Yes, three.

53
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,633
Do you have a room with an
overlooking view?

54
00:03:26,567 --> 00:03:28,900
[EDWARD] Okay guys,
this is our last hurrah

55
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:31,267
and we need
content for promotions.

56
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:39,433
[LUNA] Fine.
What content will you do?

57
00:03:39,433 --> 00:03:42,333
[Edward] Me? We'll all do it.

58
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:43,433
We'll all do it.

59
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:45,367
[JADE] Wait.
Wait a minute.

60
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,267
What are we going to do?

61
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:50,500
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,400
We'll dance.

63
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,600
We'll make a dance trend

64
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:57,933
so they can see how
happy we are at Hotel 88.

65
00:03:57,933 --> 00:04:04,867
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

66
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:07,800
[LEON] I'll pass on that.

67
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,200
Me too.

68
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:12,800
I'm sorry, Edward,
we're not yet complete

69
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,967
Justin's not here yet.

70
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:16,800
[KIKO] Martin isn't here yet,
either.

71
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:21,433
Okay, guys.
Let's practice first, okay?

72
00:04:21,433 --> 00:04:24,567
Let's just talk about
the plan later, okay?

73
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:25,900
- [EDWARD] Jade.
- Yeah?

74
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,433
- Let's start.
- Alright.

75
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:28,900
[EDWARD] Three, two, one, go.

76
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:31,033
- One, two, three, four...
- One, two, three, four...

77
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:33,633
- five, six, seven, eight.
- five, six, seven, eight.

78
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:36,267
Okay, let's stop this,
Is everyone ready?

79
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:38,567
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

80
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,367
Energy. Okay, game!

81
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,400
Three, two, one...

82
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,900
Go!

83
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,067
- One, two, three, four...
- One, two, three, four...

84
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,000
- five, six, seven, eight.
- five, six, seven, eight.

85
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,800
- [ALL] Ha!
- [SCREAMING]

86
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,367
[LUNA] Jade!

87
00:04:51,567 --> 00:04:53,467
Jade, are you alright?

88
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,700
Are you okay?

89
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,533
Uh...

90
00:04:58,533 --> 00:04:59,800
I'm fine, I'm fine.

91
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,433
- I'm okay.
- [LUNA] Sorry, Jade.

92
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:03,667
- [LUNA] I thought--
- [JADE] Let's just start over.

93
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:05,333
- Let's do it again.
- Okay.

94
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:06,800
Are you sure?

95
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,600
Three, two, one... Go!

96
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,400
- One, two, three, four...
- One, two, three, four...

97
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,033
- five, six, seven, eight.
- five, six, seven, eight.

98
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:15,000
On right!

99
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,033
- Okay.
- Okay.

100
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:19,400
Oh, come on.
We have the same vibes.

101
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,067
That's why you gave
me your IG.

102
00:05:21,067 --> 00:05:23,400
Will you just stop.

103
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:24,900
Do you not have
an Instagram account?

104
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,933
How about Messenger instead?

105
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:29,733
You don't get it, do you?
I don't want to!

106
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:32,833
[SCOFFS] You're hiding something
on social media, aren't you?

107
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,433
Interesting.

108
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:37,967
How about your phone
number instead?

109
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:39,367
No.

110
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,333
Raphie! Raphie! Raphie! Raphie!

111
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:45,800
Please tell my brother how
disrespectful his staff are!

112
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,000
- He's been...
- Staff?

113
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,367
You mean, Sir Justin? [CHUCKLES]

114
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:51,667
[RAPHIE] Before I forget,

115
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,633
they've been waiting
for you, sir.

116
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:54,933
What's going on?

117
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,700
[RAPHIE] Uh, I forgot
to tell you, Miss Trixie,

118
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:02,033
he's one of the
owners of the hotel.

119
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:04,100
Sir Justin, this is Miss Trixie.

120
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,800
Sir Martin's sister.

121
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,333
Ah! She's Martin's half-sister.

122
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:12,533
- So you're an Almazan?
- [JUSTIN CHUCKLES]

123
00:06:12,533 --> 00:06:15,533
- Miss Trixie!
- What?

124
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:18,733
I am Justin Almazan. [SMOOCHES]

125
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:21,333
- At your service.
- What are you doing?!

126
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,467
[RAPHIE] I'll take my leave...

127
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,767
Whatever. [SCOFFS]

128
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:32,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:06:35,133 --> 00:06:37,767
[JADE] I couldn't get
away from Edward earlier.

130
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,033
Where did you go?

131
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:40,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

132
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,833
- Here and there...
- Like?

133
00:06:46,433 --> 00:06:48,933
Fine, I was just asking.

134
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,600
If you don't want to
answer, then don't.

135
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,067
Enough.
We just went places.

136
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:55,533
- It's part of the job.
- Okay

137
00:06:55,533 --> 00:07:00,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:02,933
Wait a minute,
where are we going?

139
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:05,567
My dad likes to take videos.

140
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:09,067
Sometimes, videos of himself
or of his loved ones.

141
00:07:09,067 --> 00:07:12,033
Who knows, maybe...

142
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:13,633
Okay, okay.

143
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:17,033
You're right.
Mom might be there.

144
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:20,500
That would be proof if they
had an affair.

145
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:23,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES, SWELLS]

146
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:25,500
Here.

147
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,900
We're here.

148
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,200
Huh?

149
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,667
Uncle Mike's room?

150
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,800
[DOOR LOCK CLICKS]

151
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,967
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

152
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,433
Thank you, sir, ma'am.

153
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,667
Thank you very much.
Please pay us a visit again!

154
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,633
Happy anniversary!

155
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:55,967
Take care.

156
00:07:59,067 --> 00:08:00,900
What is this guy up to?

157
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:07,867
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,433
[MONETTE] Hey, Gio!

159
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:12,800
Did something happen to you?

160
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,033
Ah.

161
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:15,967
[MONETTE] Are you all right?

162
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:17,300
I'm fine.

163
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,633
Are you sure?

164
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:25,500
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:08:26,533 --> 00:08:28,900
Did the guest from 203
come out earlier?

166
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:32,067
Ah, the handsome guy.

167
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,900
He just ordered some food and
had it delivered to his room.

168
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,033
He even complimented
my cooking skills.

169
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,333
Okay.

170
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,600
Wait a second.

171
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,733
Why did you ask about him?

172
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:44,567
Do you know that guest?

173
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,667
I don't.

174
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:49,733
I don't know him.
How would I even know him?

175
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:50,900
I just asked.

176
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,067
Okay.

177
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:53,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

178
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:56,500
By the way, congratulations!

179
00:08:56,533 --> 00:09:00,500
It's only been a few days but
we're slowly filling up!

180
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,967
It seems your event
will be successful.

181
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:05,433
You know, if only
Sir Michael saw all of this,

182
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:08,067
I'm sure he'd be very excited.

183
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:10,067
- [MONETTE CLICKS TONGUE]
- I think so too.

184
00:09:10,067 --> 00:09:11,667
Okay, I'll get going then.

185
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:14,067
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:16,067
What happened to that guy?

187
00:09:19,367 --> 00:09:20,667
[MICHAEL] Hello, kids!

188
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,500
<i> - Your uncle and I are here!
</i>- [FEDERICO] Yes!

189
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,067
<i>Look, this place is
so beautiful.</i>

190
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:25,600
<i> Look at that.</i>

191
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,833
<i> Can you see it? It's so vast.</i>

192
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:29,933
<i>We'll take you here
next time, right?</i>

193
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:31,933
- [FEDRICO]<i> Yes, sir!
</i>- [MICHAEL] Oh, Frida!

194
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:35,100
<i>I'll borrow him for now, okay?
[LAUGHS]</i>

195
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,567
[FEDERICO]<i> What can we do?
</i> You don't have a wife!

196
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:38,167
[MICHAEL]<i> I'll have him
</i> to myself for a minute, okay?

197
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:41,100
<i>- But I won't take long!
- Yes, we won't take long.</i>

198
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:43,600
<i>- Uncle Mike...
- Yes... Yes.</i>

199
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,600
<i> But for now, it'll just be us.</i>

200
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,667
<i>- Right? Oh.
- Cheers!</i>

201
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:49,767
<i>Next time, we'll be with
our families, right?</i>

202
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:51,567
[MICHAEL] It's nice.
It's beautiful.

203
00:09:52,067 --> 00:09:58,067
[KIDS GIGGLING]

204
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:59,833
<i> Hey, knock him down.
Knock him down!</i>

205
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,433
<i>- Knock him down!
- I'll get back at you!</i>

206
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:02,933
<i> Ouch! Stop! Stop!</i>

207
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:04,200
[MICHAEL] Ayan!

208
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,933
<i> Go, wrestle with Gio!</i>

209
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:09,100
<i> Strengthen your bones!</i>

210
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,867
<i>Hey, it's Papa!
Make him join us!</i>

211
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:13,100
<i> - Come on, Dad!
</i>- [MICHAEL CHUCKLES]

212
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,933
<i> I'll leave all that to you.</i>

213
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:17,100
<i> - You three can handle it.
</i>- [KIDS GIGGLING]

214
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,100
<i> Don't ask me to join you.</i>

215
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,533
I'll just be your videographer.

216
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:21,833
[KIDS GIGGLING]

217
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:24,100
<i>- Come on, Pa!
- Go on.</i>

218
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,933
<i>Just keep having fun here
at the hotel.</i>

219
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:30,500
<i> - Pa, come on!
- Come join us, Pa!</i>

220
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:31,933
<i> Hey, hurry up!</i>

221
00:10:31,933 --> 00:10:34,033
[MICHAEL] Kiko, are you happy?

222
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:36,633
<i>Would you like some
more banana chips?</i>

223
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:38,967
<i> Pa, come on! Let's play here!</i>

224
00:10:38,967 --> 00:10:40,633
<i> Right, Pa. Come join us.</i>

225
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:43,100
<i>- Come on!
- Join us!</i>

226
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,533
<i> Look, it's all done.</i>

227
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:45,633
<i> I built it myself.</i>

228
00:10:45,633 --> 00:10:46,867
<i> Hey, that's crazy!</i>

229
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:48,867
[MICHAEL] I love you so much,
my sons.

230
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,000
<i> Should we make that one again?</i>

231
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,633
<i>- Sure!
- Okay then!</i>

232
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,867
<i> Hey, Pa!</i>

233
00:10:52,867 --> 00:10:55,867
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:58,067
Uncle Mike loves you very much.

235
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,733
Jade.

236
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,733
Are we still doing
the right thing?

237
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:13,633
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:15,000
Yes?

239
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:16,833
No, it's just that...

240
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:19,700
Your mother's not in
the video anyway.

241
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:22,067
Maybe that means she really
has nothing to do with it.

242
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:24,667
Or maybe, we're the only ones
who have doubts?

243
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:28,833
Didn't...

244
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:32,100
the police return
your father's phone to you?

245
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,700
Yes, because that case
was closed. Why?

247
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:38,867
[JADE] We might be able
to find something there.

248
00:11:38,867 --> 00:11:42,667
There could be something in
his messages or photo gallery.

249
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:45,000
I'll also check out
my dad's phone.

250
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:49,267
Jade, I thought we were only
investigating your mother here.

251
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:51,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

252
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:54,967
It's just that we might be able
to find something, right?

253
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:57,067
I mean, there's no harm
in trying.

254
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:02,833
Okay.

255
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:06,067
Okay, let's go with your way.

256
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:09,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,267
[FRIDA EXHALES] What is this?

258
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:12,633
[FEDERICO] Don't peek.

259
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:16,100
<i>- Federico, what is this?
- Just a little bit more.</i>

260
00:12:16,133 --> 00:12:17,900
[FEDERICO]<i> Just don't peek,
</i> please?

261
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:19,300
<i>- Okay.
- Oh, close your eyes.</i>

262
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,800
[FEDERICO]<i> I need to
</i> let you go now, okay?

263
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:21,933
[FRIDA] Alright.

264
00:12:22,567 --> 00:12:23,800
<i> Just a little bit more.</i>

265
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:24,967
<i> Five seconds.</i>

266
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:26,533
<i> Four...</i>

267
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:27,833
<i> Three...</i>

268
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:28,967
<i> Two...</i>

269
00:12:28,967 --> 00:12:30,100
<i> Don't open it.</i>

270
00:12:30,733 --> 00:12:32,733
<i> And one, surprise.</i>

271
00:12:32,733 --> 00:12:36,133
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:38,067
<i>- For me?
- Yes.</i>

273
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,700
<i> - I hope you like it.
- Mm!</i>

274
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,067
<i> I love it!</i>

275
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,067
<i>You know what they say
about that flower?</i>

276
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:49,667
<i>It only blooms when
it feels truly cared for.</i>

277
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:51,867
<i> Delicate...</i>

278
00:12:52,733 --> 00:12:54,100
<i> Rare...</i>

279
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,700
<i> Just like you, Frida.</i>

280
00:12:57,667 --> 00:12:59,267
<i> You can't be bought.</i>

281
00:13:00,133 --> 00:13:01,700
<i> You can't be owned.</i>

282
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:03,700
<i> But...</i>

283
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:06,267
<i> the only thing I can do is...</i>

284
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:09,100
<i> take care of it.</i>

285
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,833
<i> Take care of you.</i>

286
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:13,933
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

287
00:13:14,133 --> 00:13:16,700
<i> My beloved is so sweet.</i>

288
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:18,600
<i> Thanks, my love.</i>

289
00:13:18,967 --> 00:13:20,200
<i> I hope you like it.</i>

290
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,367
<i> I love it.</i>

291
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:25,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:27,200
[FRIDA] I love you.

293
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:33,033
<i> I...</i>

294
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:35,933
<i> I love you so much.</i>

295
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:47,767
[MUSIC TURNS MELANCHOLIC]

296
00:13:49,733 --> 00:13:55,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,733
[DOOR CLOSES]

298
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:03,567
[HUMMING]

299
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:05,067
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

300
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:06,500
Hi, Sir Martin.

301
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:08,900
Good evening.

302
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:13,233
You're still so noisy
even though it's late.

303
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:15,300
- Sir, I have good news.
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:18,067
Make sure it's good.
I was tired the whole day.

305
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:20,900
It's really good news, sir!

306
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,233
What is it? Tell me.

307
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:24,967
Because tomorrow...

308
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:27,067
you'll be interviewing
a new candidate

309
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:29,033
for your future assistant!

310
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:32,100
I'm really awesome!
I'm amazing, I did all that!

311
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,633
Cancel it.
Everything's fine now.

312
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,067
What do you mean?

313
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:39,300
I don't need
a new assistant.

314
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:42,267
- But you said to--
- I changed my mind.

315
00:14:42,267 --> 00:14:45,467
Everything's fine.
Cancel the interview tomorrow.

316
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:48,233
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:50,033
Good night, Raphie.

318
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:55,133
You asked me to do that,
just to cancel it?!

319
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:56,933
[MARTIN] Thanks, Raphie!

320
00:14:57,667 --> 00:15:00,133
You're so confusing!

321
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:01,367
[SIGHS]

322
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:04,600
This isn't mine...

323
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:08,667
[SARI] You know what, Grandpa,
I thought I'd lose my job.

324
00:15:08,667 --> 00:15:11,033
Sir Martin is truly
something else,

325
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:13,100
his determination is unmatched.

326
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,700
And he's so handsome.

327
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,367
He looks like an angel.

328
00:15:16,367 --> 00:15:17,600
Yuck!

329
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,733
- What do you mean, yuck?
- You said<i> anghit</i> (body odor).

330
00:15:18,733 --> 00:15:20,000
Are you saying it's annoying?

331
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:23,600
Grandpa.
I said he looks like an angel.

332
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,300
Hmm, an angel.

333
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,700
[UTENSILS CLATTERING]

334
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:29,100
Didn't you say he has a temper?

335
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,467
- And?
- Are there angels like that?

336
00:15:31,467 --> 00:15:33,467
Yes.

337
00:15:33,467 --> 00:15:35,200
Sir Martin.

338
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:37,500
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

339
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,367
- Hey, Sari.
- Oh...

340
00:15:39,367 --> 00:15:40,767
Snap out of it.

341
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:44,467
We're about to eat dinner. Hmm.

342
00:15:44,467 --> 00:15:46,367
- Grandpa...
- Hmm?

343
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:48,633
I will never forget the moment

344
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:50,467
he saved me from that rain.

345
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,200
Sari...

346
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,500
It was just rain...

347
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:57,400
it wan't a disaster.

348
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,767
He gave you an umbrella, and
you're already acting like that.

349
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:04,500
Grandpa, men like that are
hard to come by nowadays.

350
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:07,033
The type who'll let strangers
borrow their umbrella

351
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:09,067
and don't care if they get wet.

352
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:11,200
- Oh, before I forget, Sari...
- Yeah?

353
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:13,067
I'm curious.

354
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:15,167
How's the event
you're planning?

355
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:17,533
Oh, he's G for the music fest.

356
00:16:17,533 --> 00:16:19,267
- Hmm?
- It's like he'll die

357
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:20,633
It felt like he was going
to die if he didn't continue.

358
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:23,167
What do you mean by "G"?

359
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:24,700
- Game!
- Oh!

360
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,300
[CHUCKLES]

361
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:31,200
I mean, Hotel 88 is known
for being a lively place.

362
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,533
- Mhmm.
- And the dad!

363
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,667
The dad of the guy
who gave you the umbrella,

364
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:36,300
he was such a nice guy!

365
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:40,567
But then...

366
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:43,400
tragedy struck between
him and his bestfriend.

367
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,367
[CLICKS TONGUE] It's
devastating, isn't it?

368
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:50,700
They were friends who ended
up killing each other.

369
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:53,667
- They didn't kill each other.
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING, SWELLS]

370
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:57,300
What? But that's what
the police said!

371
00:16:57,300 --> 00:17:00,433
Did they tell you
something else?

372
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:02,167
I knew both of them.

373
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,267
They were good people.

374
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,500
They wouldn't kill each other.

375
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:15,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:27,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

377
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,567
Leon.

378
00:17:33,967 --> 00:17:36,467
Earlier, after the dance video
Edward made us do,

379
00:17:36,467 --> 00:17:38,100
you just disappeared.

380
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,367
I just went somewhere.

381
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:41,167
Actually, you always disappear.

382
00:17:41,167 --> 00:17:42,833
- [JUSTIN] Who wants dinner?
- Me, please.

383
00:17:43,567 --> 00:17:46,800
Dad has other businesses
that also need attention.

384
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,300
[FRIDA] Oh, hello, everyone.

385
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,367
Oh, Mom, you're still awake.

386
00:17:52,367 --> 00:17:53,400
[FRIDA] Of course.

387
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,500
[LEON] Hi, Mom.

388
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:56,500
[LUNA] Hi, Ma.

389
00:17:57,500 --> 00:18:00,133
[EXHALES] I really waited
for you to come back.

390
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:04,533
About the flowers,

391
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,033
who sent them?

392
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:09,600
Someone sent you flowers?

393
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,867
Yes, this morning.

394
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:14,167
I thought it was from Leon?

395
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:15,467
Hmm?

396
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:17,367
Justin, wasn't it from you?

397
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,533
No.

398
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:21,067
What kind of flowers
were these again, Ma?

399
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,233
Like the ones your Dad
used to give.

400
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:25,900
Before.

401
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,367
[LUNA] Waling-waling?

402
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:28,367
[FRIDA] Yes.

403
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:30,467
[LEON CLEARS THROAT]

404
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:40,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:41,633
Well, it's okay.

406
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:43,300
Maybe one of the helpers.

407
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,300
I'll ask them tomorrow.

408
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:48,033
Go ahead. Have dinner first.

409
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:49,633
I just have something
to do in my room.

410
00:18:52,233 --> 00:18:59,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

411
00:19:06,300 --> 00:19:08,667
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

412
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:15,600
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CROW CAWING]

413
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:34,400
[SPRAY HISSING]

414
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,533
[SPRAY HISSING]

415
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:42,067
[SPRAY HISSING]

416
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:46,733
[SPRAY HISSING]

417
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:53,667
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

418
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:07,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

419
00:20:16,733 --> 00:20:18,100
[MUSIC STOPS]

420
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:26,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

421
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:34,667
[DOOR OPENS]

422
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:39,767
[DOOR CLOSES]

423
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:47,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

424
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,433
- [EXHALES]
- [DRAWER OPENS]

425
00:20:58,933 --> 00:20:59,900
[EXHALES]

426
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:00,867
Dad.

427
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:02,667
Dad.

428
00:21:02,667 --> 00:21:04,867
If you're going
to make yourself felt, please...

429
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:06,033
do it now.

430
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:09,867
Show me where Mom
hid your phone.

431
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:12,900
[EXHALES]

432
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:20,200
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [OBJECT CLATTERING]

433
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,967
[DRAWER CLOSES]

434
00:21:35,233 --> 00:21:42,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

435
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,133
- Oh!
- [THUDS]

436
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:49,533
[OBJECT CLATTER]

437
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:59,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

438
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,333
[THUDS]

439
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:19,567
- [CLATTERING]
- [BREATHES HEAVILY]

440
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:29,500
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

441
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:33,133
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

442
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,333
[DOOR OPENS]

443
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,867
<i> Sari, the contract!</i>

444
00:22:42,867 --> 00:22:43,900
<i>- Oh!
- Where is it?!</i>

445
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:45,167
<i> Wait, sir, it's just here.</i>

446
00:22:46,033 --> 00:22:47,367
<i>The more you
walk away from me...</i>

447
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:49,967
<i> the more you'll see this face.</i>

448
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:51,467
<i> Oh god.</i>

449
00:22:51,467 --> 00:22:52,500
<i> Bro, is this yours?</i>

450
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,067
<i> Is this your missing car?</i>

451
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:55,267
<i> Huh--</i>

452
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:56,633
[BLOW LANDS]

453
00:22:56,633 --> 00:22:58,167
[WATER SPLASHES]

454
00:22:58,167 --> 00:23:01,033
<i>- Welcome to Hotel 88, sir!
- Here comes Edward Arellano!</i>

455
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:03,000
The four of us should be united.

456
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,400
<i> We can't fall apart.</i>

457
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,633
<i> But now,
there's only three of us.</i>

458
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:06,700
<i> Where is Jade anyway?</i>

459
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:09,567
<i> Flowers!
Someone gave Mom flowers!</i>

460
00:23:09,567 --> 00:23:11,000
<i> It's waling-waling.</i>

461
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,067
<i>I know someone who takes care
of that kind of plant.</i>

462
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:15,067
<i> Is anyone there?</i>

463
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,000
<i> - Hello?!
- Kiko-- Kiko, wait.</i>

464
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,400
<i> I think I know this place.</i>

